    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/53a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Governor of Arizona</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Mexican Embassy has informed the Department of State that the President of
                    Mexico has convoked an extraordinary session of the Mexican Congress in order to
                    secure authorization for requesting permission from the Government of the United
                    States to transport Mexican Federal troops from Ciudad Juárez to points in the
                    State of Sonora to cope with the situation in that State where American life and
                    property are in serious danger from the operations of Mexican revolutionary
                    bands. Before the issuance of definite instructions, in the event that the
                    Mexican Government requests permission to transport its troops through United
                    States territory for the purpose mentioned, I have the honor to request that you
                    telegraph me, in accordance with the customary formality, the assurance that
                    this course will be entirely agreeable to the State of Arizona.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p rend="center">[<hi rend="italic">Mutatis mutandis</hi> to the Governors of
                        Texas and New Mexico.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
